    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: ROCKWELL WABCO 4 CHANNEL - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>ABS</title>
            <para>Signals from the wheel speed sensors are received and processed by the electronic control unit (ECU).
                When the ECU determines a wheel is going to a lock condition, the appropriate modulator valve is
                activated and brake pressure is reduced. When the wheel speed enters the stable region again, the brake
                pressure is automatically increased.
            </para>
            <para>If there is a failure in the ABS, the vehicle reverts to normal braking.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
